### Get assigned isolation segment

```
Definition
```

```http
GET /v3/spaces/:guid/relationships/isolation_segment HTTP/1.1
```

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/spaces/[guid]/relationships/isolation_segment" \
  -X GET \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]"
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :space_isolation_segment_relationship, '/v3/spaces' %>
```

Retrieve the isolation segment currently assigned to the space.
